## 🐛 Bug Report

While trying to load the attached [Dummy File.xlsx](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/19954237/Dummy.File.xlsx) using `xlsx.load`, the browser is getting out of memory

Lib version: 4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce

```javascript
const readExcelFile = (file) => {
  const ExcelWorkbook = new ExcelJs.Workbook();
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    const reader = new FileReader();
    reader.onload = (e) => {
      ExcelWorkbook.xlsx.load(e.target?.result).then((workbookIns) => {
        resolve(workbookIns);
      });
     };
    reader.onerror = (error) => {
      reject(error);
    };
    reader.readAsArrayBuffer(file);
  });
};
```

## The expected behaviour:

The file to get loaded and the promise to resolve, but it is getting stuck inside `load`

## Where the issue resides:

After debugging, I found out that inside the load function, this is where it is getting out of memory
```javascript
this.workbook.model = model;
```
